&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frailty Assessment Unit – Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 - £24,907 - £30,615 (pro rata)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 hrs per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for enthusiastic Staff Nurses to join the dynamic Frailty Team. The Frailty Service consists of a 16 bedded short stay ward and an assessment unit situated at the front door. Staff are able to rotate between both areas. Frailty is a rapidly growing specialism that aims to reduce hospitalisation for frail and elderly patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a developing service and we are searching for motivated and enthusiastic individuals. Ideally you would have a background in Frailty or Elderly Care but we would welcome applications from any interested candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Nurse Rebecca Holmes-Fairclough Ext 4244&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Or Matron Rachael Collins Elderly Care/Frailty - Tel: 01384 456111 Ext 3307&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
